reviews.text: I am a paralysed a person  going on my electric wheelchair and I had a problem with getting help yesterday :-(
Had no problem obtaining my Greater Anglia ticket from the machine. Helpful staff.

Me and my family went to southend yesterday we got off at southend central my mum disabled in a wheelchair liverpool street rung though for a ramp when we got there but when  we were coming back a out 4.30ish no one is about but noone told us that there would be no ramp on the way back so passengers kindly lefted my mum out of the wheelchair onto the train when we got to liverpool street my auntie had to run to get a ramp my mum was so stressed out we should of been told when we were at southe d central that no one would be there this is disgusting for disabled people I just want u to look in to it my mum is still stress now

What a joke one machine no staff and a que that's a joke poor show when only one train line is working properly. Up your game Southend central we are paying customers. But i saw 4 security guys on the other platform checking tickets......
No staff at the station. Ended up having to pay Twice for my tickets because I couldn't get my returns printed off. What a joke.
